---
title: DMCN Message Lifecycle
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant AC as Alice's Client
    participant IR as Identity Registry
    participant R1 as Relay Node 1
    participant R2 as Relay Node 2
    participant R3 as Relay Node 3
    participant ST as Message Store
    participant BC as Bob's Client

    AC->>IR: Lookup bob@example.com
    IR-->>AC: Bob's public key(s)

    Note over AC: 1. Compose plaintext_message
    Note over AC: 2. Sign with Alice's Ed25519 private key
    Note over AC: 3. Generate random CEK
    Note over AC: 4. Encrypt payload with CEK (AES-256-GCM)
    Note over AC: 5. Wrap CEK for each of Bob's device sub-keys
    Note over AC: 6. Assemble encrypted_envelope
    Note over AC: 7. Wrap in 3-layer onion packet

    AC->>R1: Onion packet (layer 1)
    R1->>IR: Verify Alice's sender signature
    IR-->>R1: Signature valid ✓

    alt Signature invalid or sender unregistered
        R1-->>AC: Drop — no delivery failure returned
    end

    R1->>R2: Onion packet (layer 2 — R1 knows only next hop)
    R2->>R3: Onion packet (layer 3 — R2 knows only next hop)
    R3->>ST: Store encrypted_envelope for Bob

    Note over R1,R3: No relay node can read message content
    Note over R1,R3: No relay node knows both origin and destination

    BC->>ST: Authenticate + fetch message headers
    ST-->>BC: stored_message_record headers
    BC->>ST: Fetch encrypted_envelope
    ST-->>BC: encrypted_envelope

    Note over BC: 1. Locate recipient_record matching device sub-key
    Note over BC: 2. X25519 exchange → unwrap CEK
    Note over BC: 3. Decrypt payload with CEK
    Note over BC: 4. Verify Alice's Ed25519 signature
    Note over BC: 5. Display message ✓

    BC-->>AC: delivery_receipt (optional, encrypted to Alice)
